<title>USA: CBT Group plans acquisition.</title>
<headline>CBT Group plans acquisition.</headline>
<dateline>MENLO PARK, Calif. 1996-11-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>CBT Group Plc said on Monday it has agreed to acquire Applied Learning Limited, an Australian distributor of interactive education software, for US$10 million in CBT's American Depositary Shares.</p>
<p>Applied Learning is based in New South Wales, Australia, and it is CBT's exclusive software distributor in Australia and New Zealand.</p>
<p>The acquisition is to be consummated under Australian law. It is subject to approval of the Supreme Court of New South Wales and a 75-percent vote by Applied Learning shareholders.</p>
<p>The deal is expected to be accounted for as a pooling of interests and will close on or before the end of February 1997.</p>
<p>CBT Group's shares ended up 2 at 54-3/4 on Tuesday.</p>
